  "texts": [
    "In the context of mobile phone data processing, civil society organizations have pointed out how mobile phones are often used by multiple people, leading to contradictory and wrong assessments.",
    "Finally, it is questionable whether speech or dialect recognition is a suitable method to prove \"fraud of ID documents and narratives\" 139 in asylum procedures, as it currently is in Germany.",
    "Resorting to the concept of evidence has relevant legal consequences for two reasons.",
    "First, the law sets admissibility standards and rules to collect evidence that applies to automated evidence.",
    "For instance, in the context of asylum procedures, the Qualification Directive 140 sets out evidence rules for assessing facts and circumstances in applications for international protection."
